returns._0: The unique identifier for this account implementation.

checkERC7739Support(bytes32,bytes).details: For automatic detection that the smart account supports the ERC7739 workflow Iterates over all the validators but only if this is a detection request ERC-7739 spec assumes that if the account doesn't support ERC-7739 it will try to handle the detection request as it was normal sig verification request and will return 0xffffffff since it won't be able to verify the 0x signature against 0x7739...7739 hash. So this approach is consistent with the ERC-7739 spec. If no validator supports ERC-7739, this function returns false thus the account will proceed with normal signature verification and return 0xffffffff as a result.

entryPoint().details: This function returns the address of the canonical ERC4337 EntryPoint contract. It can be overridden to return a different EntryPoint address if needed.

returns._0: The address of the EntryPoint contract.

execute(bytes32,bytes).details: This function handles transaction execution flexibility and is protected by the `onlyEntryPoint` modifier.This function also goes through hook checks via withHook modifier.

params.executionCalldata: The encoded transaction data to execute.
params.mode: The execution mode detailing how transactions should be handled (single, batch, default, try/catch).

executeFromExecutor(bytes32,bytes).details: This function is callable only by an executor module and goes through hook checks.

params.mode: The execution mode (single or batch, default or try).

returns.returnData: The results of the transaction executions, which may include errors in try mode.

executeUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,byt.details: Only callable by the EntryPoint. Decodes the user operation calldata, skipping the first four bytes, and executes the inner call.

params.userOp: The user operation to execute, containing transaction details.

returns.hook: The address of the active hook module.

returns.result: The current balance held at the EntryPoint.

getExecutorsPaginated(address,uint256).details: Retrieves a paginated list of executor addresses from the linked list. This utility function is not defined by the ERC-7579 standard and is implemented to facilitate easier management and retrieval of large sets of executor modules.

params.cursor: The address to start pagination from, or zero to start from the first entry.
params.size: The number of executor addresses to return.

returns.next: The address to use as a cursor for the next page of results.

returns._0: calltype The type of call that the handler manages.
returns._1: handler The address of the fallback handler.

returns.implementation: The address of the current contract implementation.

getValidatorsPaginated(address,uint256).details: Retrieves a paginated list of validator addresses from the linked list. This utility function is not defined by the ERC-7579 standard and is implemented to facilitate easier management and retrieval of large sets of validator modules.

params.cursor: The address to start pagination from, or zero to start from the first entry.
params.size: The number of validator addresses to return.

returns.next: The address to use as a cursor for the next page of results.

initializeAccount(bytes).details: This function can only be called by the account itself or the proxy factory. When a 7702 account is created, the first userOp should contain self-call to initialize the account.

params.initData: The initialization data for the smart account.

installModule(uint256,address,bytes).details: This function can only be called by the EntryPoint or the account itself for security reasons.This function goes through hook checks via withHook modifier through internal function _installModule.

params.module: The address of the module to install.
params.moduleTypeId: The type identifier of the module being installed, which determines its role: - 1 for Validator - 2 for Executor - 3 for Fallback - 4 for Hook - 8 for 1271 Prevalidation Hook - 9 for 4337 Prevalidation Hook

isInitialized().details: In case default validator is initialized, two other SLOADS from _areSentinelListsInitialized() are not checked, this method should not introduce huge gas overhead.

returns._0: True if the smart account is initialized, false otherwise.

params.additionalContext: Optional context that may be needed for certain checks.
params.module: The address of the module to check.
params.moduleTypeId: The ID corresponding to the type of module (Validator, Executor, Fallback, Hook).

returns._0: True if the module is installed, false otherwise.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Delegates the validation to a validator module specified within the signature data.

params.hash: The hash of the data being validated.
params.signature: Signature data that needs to be validated.

returns._0: The status code of the signature validation (`0x1626ba7e` if valid). bytes4(keccak256("isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes)") = 0x1626ba7e
The nonce associated with the key.

proxiableUUID().details: Returns the storage slot used by the implementation, as specified in [ERC1822](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1822). Note: The `notDelegated` modifier prevents accidental upgrades to an implementation that is a proxy contract.

setRegistry(address,address[],uint8).details: This function can only be called by the EntryPoint or the account itself.

returns.isSupported: True if the execution mode is supported, false otherwise.

params.moduleTypeId: The identifier of the module type to check.

returns._0: True if the module type is supported, false otherwise.

uninstallModule(uint256,address,bytes).details: Ensures that the operation is authorized and valid before proceeding with the uninstallation.

params.module: The address of the module to uninstall.
params.moduleTypeId: The type ID of the module to be uninstalled, matching the installation type: - 1 for Validator - 2 for Executor - 3 for Fallback - 4 for Hook - 8 for 1271 Prevalidation Hook - 9 for 4337 Prevalidation Hook

params.data: The calldata to be sent to the new implementation.
params.newImplementation: The address of the new contract implementation.

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: Expects the validator's address to be encoded in the upper 96 bits of the user operation's nonce. This method forwards the validation task to the extracted validator module address.The entryPoint calls this function. If validation fails, it returns `VALIDATION_FAILED` (1) otherwise `0`.Features Module Enable Mode. This Module Enable Mode flow is intended for the module acting as the validator for the user operation that triggers the Module Enable Flow. Otherwise, a call to `Nexus.installModule` should be included in `userOp.callData`.

params.missingAccountFunds: Funds missing from the account's deposit necessary for transaction execution. This can be zero if covered by a paymaster or if sufficient deposit exists.
params.op: The user operation to validate, encapsulating all transaction details.
params.userOpHash: Hash of the user operation data, used for signature validation.

returns.validationData: Encoded validation result or failure, propagated from the validator module. - Encoded format in validationData:     - First 20 bytes: Address of the Validator module, to which the validation task is forwarded.       The validator module returns:         - `SIG_VALIDATION_SUCCESS` (0) indicates successful validation.         - `SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED` (1) indicates signature validation failure.

params.to: The address to receive the withdrawn funds.

addDeposit().notice: Adds deposit to the EntryPoint to fund transactions.

constructor.notice: Initializes the smart account with the specified entry point.

entryPoint().notice: Retrieves the address of the EntryPoint contract, currently using version 0.7.

execute(bytes32,bytes).notice: Executes transactions in single or batch modes as specified by the execution mode.

executeFromExecutor(bytes32,bytes).notice: Executes transactions from an executor module, supporting both single and batch transactions.

executeUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,byt.notice: Executes a user operation via a call using the contract's context.

getActiveHook().notice: Retrieves the currently active hook address.

getDeposit().notice: Returns the current deposit balance of this account on the EntryPoint.

getFallbackHandlerBySelector(bytes4).notice: Fetches the fallback handler for a specific selector.

getImplementation().notice: Retrieves the address of the current implementation from the EIP-1967 slot.Checks the 1967 implementation slot, if not found then checks the slot defined by address (Biconomy V2 smart account)

initializeAccount(bytes).notice: Initializes the smart account with the specified initialization data.

installModule(uint256,address,bytes).notice: Installs a new module to the smart account.

isInitialized().notice: Checks if the smart account is initialized.

isModuleInstalled(uint256,address,bytes).notice: Determines whether a module is installed on the smart account.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).notice: Validates a signature according to ERC-1271 standards.

nonce(uint192).notice: Gets the nonce for a particular key.

setRegistry(address,address[],uint8).notice: Sets the registry for the smart account.

supportsExecutionMode(bytes32).notice: Determines if a specific execution mode is supported.

supportsModule(uint256).notice: Checks if a specific module type is supported by this smart account.

uninstallModule(uint256,address,bytes).notice: Uninstalls a module from the smart account.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).notice: Upgrades the contract to a new implementation and calls a function on the new contract.Updates two slots 1. ERC1967 slot and 2. address() slot in case if it's potentially upgraded earlier from Biconomy V2 account, as Biconomy v2 Account (proxy) reads implementation from the slot that is defined by its address

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.notice: Validates a user operation against a specified validator, extracted from the operation's nonce.

withdrawDepositTo(address,uint256).notice: Withdraws ETH from the EntryPoint to a specified address.
